OL,3,CFears over safety at night grow ahead
OL,4,Cof Ramadan after Bristol stabbings
OL,6,FWith Ramadan starting on March 10,
OL,7,FMohamed A Sayaqle, Chair of Bristol
OL,8,FSomali Youth Voice, told ITV News West
OL,9,FCountry there are concerns regarding
OL,10,Fthe safety of young people returning
OL,11,Ffrom prayers late at night.
OL,13,FHe said: "A lot of young people from
OL,14,Fethnic minority backgrounds,
OL,15,Fespecially from Muslim backgrounds
OL,16,Fwill be coming out late in the evening
OL,17,Ffor prayer.
OL,19,F"They will hang out outside the mosque
OL,20,Fbefore they go to their homes."
